class Solution {
    public int maxArea(int[] height) {
        int max_area=0;
        int left=0;
        int right=height.length-1;
        while(left<right){
            max_area=Math.max(max_area,(right-left)*Math.min(height[left],height[right]));
            if(height[left]<height[right]){
                left++;
            }
            else{
                right--;;
            }
        }
        return max_area;
    }
}


**thought process**

=>initialize the max_area with 0 and assign left=0 and right is the length of the hieght-1
=> until left <right we have to loop it meanwhile calculate max_area applying logic
=>after getting max_area check using control construct if heght of left < height of right 
then will increase the left else increase right
=>after eaching the condition where left>right will return max_area
